<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_a8d2d134-f4ef-463b-85b0-e412fe9a1bd5" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="TAS"><sptc>C4D11</sptc><title id="_dba0f6aa-6e4c-4842-9d8b-de0f48d15ed3">Straining traps</title><archive-num>2019: H202.4d</archive-num><subclause id="_9368b094-8d0f-4810-b193-5499dc4b55ef" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_85cbfb41-f312-445e-b289-4ed7c1dde07f">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>The straining trap must be connected and authorised by the Permit Authority.</p></subclause><subclause id="_3a25eb53-0ca8-4052-ba05-343fcb5849dc" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_ae91af13-cb61-4401-b43a-53213791879d">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>The straining pit basket must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_9f6aec5d-f704-49b8-90a6-748423455d2e">be constructed of mild steel wire with a minimum of 2.5 mm woven to give 7 mm aperture widths on a 32 mm x 32 mm x 25 mm angle iron frame with mitred corners with a top frame of welded angle iron; or</li><li id="_a09b95bf-f6b3-49f5-b1d6-829f3ce43aa2">be constructed from minimum 3 mm thick mild steel plate, with 6 mm holes at 12 mm centres over the entire area of the basket; and</li><li id="_66ce2cd0-35d4-47d7-89ba-7d79db577beb">be hot dipped galvanised after fabrication.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_ac6a1a4b-6ce9-4528-94af-98feb97c9d66" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_e254aae4-dc32-4c92-b7c9-0a9a0428bd45">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>If the straining trap is to be used in installations connected to the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1376_4.2.0.xml#_12d6153c-4986-4856-80c0-e21bb57af12f" id="_a5282048-5c30-4b3b-bc94-0102b0179846" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Network Utility Operator's</xref> sewerage system, it must comply with the requirements of the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1376_4.2.0.xml#_12d6153c-4986-4856-80c0-e21bb57af12f" id="_f8a3b56d-4c1b-4d38-86d5-65eb54163141" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Network Utility Operator's</xref> guidelines for pre-treatment devices.</p></subclause><callout id="_61041cbf-3fdd-4448-99da-e32d656fe3bf"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>See <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/7750_0.3.0.xml#_6cb3de6e-2282-4313-99a8-6472f6b8f871" id="_40c2bf7f-23d8-4ba2-ae1f-175896dab7f8" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">TAS Figure C4D11</xref> for a typical straining trap.</p><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/7750_0.3.0.xml" id="_6cb3de6e-2282-4313-99a8-6472f6b8f871" variation="TAS"><num/><title id="_f73e72ac-fc08-40d4-83ad-75cfc60b9564"/></image-reference></callout></clause>